                  "section": "Notes",
                  "excerpt": "Stacks with Intensify , Blind Rage , Transient Fortitude , Power Drift , Energy Conversion and Growing Power for a total of +298% Ability Strength (when 4 Growing Power are active +373% Ability Strength )."
                }
              },
              {
                "reviewStatus": "draft",
                "provenance": {
                  "source": "local-wiki-sqlite",
                  "pageTitle": "Augur Secrets",
                  "pageId": 1214988,
                  "revisionId": 2722109,
                  "section": "Notes",
                  "excerpt": "Replacing Intensify with Umbral Intensify , Umbral Vitality , and Umbral Fiber will grant a total of +334% Ability Strength , or +409% Ability Strength when 4 Growing Power are active."
                }
              },
              {
                "reviewStatus": "draft",
                "provenance": {
                  "source": "local-wiki-sqlite",
                  "pageTitle": "Augur Secrets",
                  "pageId": 1214988,
                  "revisionId": 2722109,
                  "section": "Notes",
                  "excerpt": "Seems like the best way to farm Augur Secrets is to play the level 30-50 Cetus Bounty . This requires Mastery Rank 3 or higher. The mission's 4th and 5th stages have a 2.20% and 5.41% chance of dropping respectively during Pool B (this refreshes every cycle or 2.5 hours). If you do not see it in the level 30-50 rare drop, you will want to wait for another cycle to attain this mod. Whilst it can drop from the Recon Commander , the drop chance of 0.5% is less than ideal."
                }
              }
